[2
Date: Wed, 26 May 1999 17:39:41 +0300
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

I ran this through the GIDEON software program. Assuming a single
infectious diseases, the differential diagnosis might also include
trichinosis, loiasis (is this the 'filaria' tested for ?), toxocariasis and
HIV infection. Eosinophilia is not a feature of trypanosomiasis per se.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
*******
[3
Date: Wed, 26 May 1999 15:53:16 -0500
From: Dr. Norman Ronald <n-ronald@TVMDL.TAMU.EDU>

The Associate Differential Diagnostic Knowledge Base for Infectious and
Parasitic Diseases of Man suggests the following diseases be considered in
the undiagnosed case for Nigeria:
Brucellosis
Loa loa infection
African Trypanosomiasis
Cat Scratch Disease
--
N.C. Ronald PhD
Editor in Chief
TVMDL- Texas A&M University
College Station, Texas 77843
e-mail: n-ronald@tamu.edu
