[4
Date: Wed, 26 May 1999 17:42:48 -0700
From: Robert S. Lewis <macaque@bigfoot.com>

Was the patient in contact with these monkeys at any time and/or with their
body
fluids? Many species of the Subfamily Cercopithecinae (baboons, macaques,
mangabeys, Patas monkeys, etc) actively shed the Herpes B virus, which is a
mere
annoyance to the monkey but deadly to humans. Does anyone on the list know
how
effective anti-viral therapy is after the patient becomes symptomatic?
When is
the best time to start anti-viral therapy?
--
Robert S. Lewis
Co-Manager alloprimate mailing list
e-mail: macaque@bigfoot.com
